HEADWORD: Sarplar
<hw>Sar"plar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. LL.
<ets>sarplare</ets>. See <er>Sarplier</er>.]</ety> <def>A large bale or
package of wool, containing eighty tods, or 2,240 pounds, in
weight.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
